    "header_color": "magenta",
    "pages": [
      {
        "page": 1,
        "total_pages": 2,
        "content": [
          "The TRAPASSATO PROSSIMO = past in the",
          "past. Something that HAD HAPPENED",
          "before another past event.",
          "",
          "FORMULA: imperfetto of avere/essere",
          "         + past participle",
          "",
          "WITH AVERE:",
          "   avevo mangiato = I had eaten",
          "   avevi detto = you had said",
          "   aveva scritto = he/she had written",
          "   avevamo finito = we had finished",
          "",
          "WITH ESSERE (same verbs as passato p.):",
          "   ero andato/a = I had gone",
          "   era arrivato/a = he/she had arrived",
          "   eravamo partiti/e = we had left"
        ],
        "pronunciation": "Ero già partito."
      },
      {
        "page": 2,
        "total_pages": 2,
        "content": [
          "WHY IT MATTERS — sequence of tenses:",
          "",
          "   Quando sono arrivato, Maria",
          "   era già partita.",
          "   = When I arrived, Maria had",
          "     already left.",
          "",
          "   Mi ha detto che aveva visto",
          "   il film la sera prima.",
          "   = He told me he had seen the",
          "     film the evening before.",
          "",
          "PATTERN: one past event happened",
          "BEFORE another past event.",
          "   passato prossimo = the later one",
          "   trapassato = the earlier one",
          "",
          "This is the backbone of storytelling."
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
